All the Plans is Starsailor's fourth studio album. It was announced on October, 2008 and will be released on March 09, 2009.
Initially named "All the Plans" or "Boy in Waiting" the album title was revealed on October 16, 2008. This release will be Starsailor's first album with Virgin Records Starsailor has worked with Steve Osborne who has previously worked with them for the release of their debut album Love Is Here and with engineer Dan Austin who was also working with Doves at the same time.
According to the band messages Starsailor's new album would be a mixture between their heavier side and the romantic side shown in their previous albums.
